dataId.description: A unique identifier for a predicate in the rule, such as Byte Match Set ID or IPSet ID.

negated.description:
Set this to `false` if you want to allow, block, or count requests
based on the settings in the specified waf_byte_match_set, waf_ipset, aws_waf_size_constraint_set, aws.waf.SqlInjectionMatchSet or aws_waf_xss_match_set.
For example, if an IPSet includes the IP address `192.0.2.44`, AWS WAF will allow or block requests based on that IP address.
If set to `true`, AWS WAF will allow, block, or count requests based on all IP addresses except `192.0.2.44`.

type.description: The type of predicate in a rule. Valid values: `ByteMatch`, `GeoMatch`, `IPMatch`, `RegexMatch`, `SizeConstraint`, `SqlInjectionMatch`, or `XssMatch`.
